What are the odds that the Discord idea was a similar idea?  Basically you put together a situation which would be most likely to bring in people who use hacks.  A situation where there is a reward for being &quot;the best&quot; in a very competitive environment and where cheating would be extremely helpful.  Because its so competitive you also have the active help of the noncheating population to identify cheating.  This could allow you to get pretty much every form of cheating out into one temporary server where you don't have to worry about the long term effects on the game or economy.  Since its a short term event the logs can't be TOO impossibly huge at least compared to regular servers, and you don't have to worry about new information to deal with after its terminated.  This sets up a situation where they can set a team aside to analyze the event in depth to look for both hacking/cheat mechanisms and cheaters themselves.  And the best part is that after you have identified the cheats you don't even have to look hard for the cheaters.  You've already got them.  When you kill the accounts that cheated on this server, you also get their characters on their home servers as well.<br>
What do you guys think?  Am I just being optimistic as to the intellegence of the Sony team?  Is my logic fuzzy?  Is this an idea thats already accepted and i'm simply slow to the punch?<br>
